  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">National and Community Capacity Strengthening to Enhance Prevention and Response to Emerging Health Threats in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to the national and local efforts undertaken in the response to potential disease outbreaks, particularly in light of the ongoing Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) epidemic and COVID-19 in the neighboring DRC, as well as national disasters in Burundi in terms of health and border management capacities at the national and subnational levels.  The project will support the Ministry of Health at the national level through procurement equipment and material to facilitate and strengthen surveillance and oversight for EVD preparedness. The project will also provide the Ministry of Security and Disaster Management, specifically the immigration department in charge of border management, with essential equipment to strengthen and facilitate border management coordination between the central and the local levels and reinforce the level of the preparedness against EVD and other communicable diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
